og.title: null Council of Economic Advisers Chairman Alan Krueger Interviewed on Bloomberg
og.description: We are joined right now by Alan Krueger, the chairman of the Council of Economic Advisors. He is the White House chief economist, and this is his last day on the job. So Dr. Krueger, congratulations on leaving the White House, but it is up to you right now to defend these somewhat disappointing jobs numbers. What do you attribute the weakness to?
